main event: A round, red object with a small trail was observed in the sky over Cayucos, California on September 2, 1957.
interesting points: The object was observed by a civilian witness in Cayucos, California.
The object was observed for about 0.50 hour (30 minutes).
The object was observed during dusk conditions.
The witness used binoculars to observe the object.
The object was determined to likely be the planet Venus, which was unusual during that time of year.
sighted object: a round, red object with a small trail
